In RAS one measures, at nearly normal incidence, the difference of the sample reflectance (ΔR) for light linearly polarized alternatively along two perpendicular directions (α and β), then reporting the ratio between ΔR and the average sample reflectance (R) as a function of wavelength:ΔR/R=2(Rα-Rβ)/(Rα+Rβ)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
